WEBVTT

00:00:00.980 --> 00:00:05.299
Hi, I'm Taylor, and this is Iron, Sharpen's Iron.

00:00:05.299 --> 00:00:18.839
Today, we're going to practice how to start a conversation that could lead to a witness.

00:00:18.839 --> 00:00:22.839
Now, for many, this can be terrifying.

00:00:22.839 --> 00:00:23.839
Why?

00:00:23.839 --> 00:00:29.320
Well, as soon as we see someone that we'd like to talk to, we can start to think to ourselves,

00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:30.839
what am I going to say?

00:00:30.839 --> 00:00:32.439
How am I going to give a witness?

00:00:32.439 --> 00:00:34.240
Or how are they going to react?

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:40.280
And we can become so overwhelmed with anxiety or nerves, thinking about how the conversation

00:00:40.280 --> 00:00:43.880
will end that we never even start.

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:47.119
So here's something that we must keep in mind.

00:00:47.119 --> 00:00:52.759
Our goal is simply to start a conversation.

00:00:52.759 --> 00:00:56.000
So if we've started a conversation, we've succeeded.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
We've reached our goal.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.320
Then we can just relax and see if it leads to a witness.

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:11.680
The September 2018 life and ministry meeting workbook shows us how we can start a conversation

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:17.359
like Jesus did with the Samaritan woman in John chapter 4.

00:01:17.359 --> 00:01:21.719
So when we see someone that we would like to talk to, we want to keep these three steps

00:01:21.719 --> 00:01:23.719
in mind.

00:01:23.719 --> 00:01:27.840
Number one, be friendly.

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:29.000
That's it.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:31.000
Just be friendly.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:35.560
So we can be nervous, so we can say quick prayer to Jehovah to give us courage, but then

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:38.760
we can give a friendly greeting.

00:01:38.760 --> 00:01:42.040
Then we can mention something that's happening right then and there.

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:47.879
Maybe the weather, the long line at the grocery store, their nice car, or another genuine

00:01:47.879 --> 00:01:49.879
compliment.

00:01:49.879 --> 00:01:54.840
Jesus, when he started his conversation in verse 7 with the Samaritan woman, he simply

00:01:54.840 --> 00:02:00.280
said, and no doubt in a friendly way, give me a drink.

00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:05.879
Step two, let the conversation progress naturally.

00:02:05.879 --> 00:02:07.840
Don't rush it.

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:12.319
If the conversation ends before we're able to give a witness, it's okay.

00:02:12.319 --> 00:02:13.400
We accomplished our goal.

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:15.439
We started a conversation.

00:02:15.439 --> 00:02:17.240
Now we're ready to try again.

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:22.879
Now, if the conversation continues on, then we can look for an opportunity to take step

00:02:22.879 --> 00:02:24.199
three.

00:02:24.199 --> 00:02:28.439
Make a simple expression of our faith.

00:02:28.439 --> 00:02:35.199
One of verses after Jesus started the conversation with the Samaritan woman, then he witnessed

00:02:35.199 --> 00:02:36.199
to her.

00:02:36.199 --> 00:02:39.919
He said he had water that imparts everlasting life.

00:02:39.919 --> 00:02:43.639
But between those two points, he didn't lecture her.

00:02:43.639 --> 00:02:49.439
He let her talk and express herself and he listened to what she had to say.

00:02:49.439 --> 00:02:53.479
So with those three steps in mind, now it's our turn.

00:02:53.479 --> 00:02:59.560
It's our turn to practice starting a conversation that could lead to a witness.

